author: @aaa_aaa_220
text:
ワルツ東京・大阪参戦しました
1曲目がこれなのほんとにぶち上がる
ANTHEMでじわじわ高まったところにこれが流れ始めて8人が登場した瞬間、ぶわあああって鳥肌と涙が…歌い出しのチャンビンでさらに号泣
今年新卒で社会人になり正直辛いことも多い日々ですが、このアルバム、この曲に励まされながら乗り越えてきた一日一日のことが思い出されて…ああ、自分はこの瞬間のために日々頑張って生きてこれたんだな、と後から後から涙がこぼれました
つらかったこと、歯食いしばって頑張ってきたことが一気に報われた気がしました
スキズの存在と曲たちがほんとに支えです
そしてスキズらしさ全開この曲が本当に大好き、ライブ終わっちゃって喪失感すごいけど明日からもこれ聞いて自分を奮い立たせながら頑張ります（；_；）

author: @RoseGRX
text:
First akgaes spread rumors again. This is nothing new or unexpected. You have to understand cause and effect. Cause 1.
Risabae nim has stated many times on YT that her Bias is Felix. She appreciates him and likes the happiness he brings. 2. She is well known in Korea and is a famous YouTuber. Result: JYPE got this information and invited her to collaborate with them on a program. Naturally, they chose Felix. So Risabae nim have agreed in a second. No cause, no effect. If Risabae never stated that her 1st bias is Felix and continued to support and publicize it on various platforms. Then this collaboration would never have happened. Whether or not it's an invitation from the company to collaborate, the only person this collaboration could be with is Felix.

author: @allill
text:
from fanbase report4flx
Akgaes are harassing FELIX with support of the fandom. Risabae has not only been a long time Fan of FLX, but her makeup video of FLX look became viral everywhere. Reached to him, managers, members. There are cases where certain hosts mention or bias Felix, but other members appear on their show. We dont twist this to make it seem like something was taken from FLX, bc this only pits members & fans against each other and starts fights. Its also MANIPULATION since they are also cropping scenarios to make it look like only JYP sent FLX there as a “favour” to “push him”, But Both host and staff wanted him and this was PROVEN (FLX was picked to appear in the show "jewel box" said by both host & Staffs! You are letting Akgae mindset take over & allowing them to spread tremendous vitriol against FLX on every SNS, official, fan pages which is unacceptable for any normal mind). Same with Risabae, who was already a huge fan also was going viral with Felix makeover look. JYP saw the opportunity to promote SKZ new album so they contacted her. This is only normalising the inhumane harassment of FLX, a member of SKZ, whose fandom continues to fail him time and time again.
P. S Having 43 accounts on a random day to report is insane.

author: @nnotmixxofficial
text:
About the plot, I think Skz is representing the greek/roman gods, specially Zeus/Jupiter. Here are some topics about this:
- Zeus (roman counterpart Jupiter) is the king of the gods and the god of the sky (not the sky itself) in greek mythology. He can control lightings, something that appear a lot of times in the MV. Another thing that represents Zeus is skz controlling situations from the sky, like moving biuldings or cars.
- The Mount Olympus is probably the mountain they want to climb, the highest point of the world and the palace of Zeus.
- The greocery store which appears in the start of the video with Changbin/Hyunjin is called Olympus Mons, standing for Mount Olympus

author: @juliaburrell2398
text: So my daughter introduced me to Kpop a few years ago and Stray Kids were my very first group. They were also beginning their journey after debuting so I feel blessed as I have had the opportunity to "grow up" with them (funny bc I am an "old" mom☺️)and witness their progression both professionally and in their personal lives (as much as they share). They will always be so special in my heart and I wish nothing but the best for them even tho I am a fan of other groups as well. They have worked hard to achieve what they have and I only hope they continue to receive Love no matter what. The cancel culture is still confusing to me as I grew up in the 60's and 70's and I suppose that whole sense of freedom for artist's lives is my foundation so I guess that's why I find it disturbing the way they are forced to have to live their lives being so scrutinized for every little thing they say, wear or do in such a harsh manner. The number of suicides in the entertainment industry for Korean artists is heartbreaking.  So what I wish for, for these young talented Korean ppl in every aspect of the entertainment industry is happiness and acceptance. As fans, let us show them that Love and simply appreciate all their hard work that goes into what they do to share with us their love of music that brings us so much joy!! Celebrating Stray Kids every day💞💞💞

author: @liza_pet
text:
Seungmin has such awesome images from 
a killer to punk rock and a fashion prince, absolutely everything suits him insanely, 
although with such a model appearance it 
is not surprising, and what unrealistic vibes 
and plasticity of every movement during choreography it is impossible to admire, 
how many facets and possibilities of his 
voice he shows and reveals in each new 
album is amazing.

author: @liza_pet
text:
He knows what he's good at and uses it to the fullest, it's really impossible to resist Seungmin, his visual literally glows, his natural charm, his crazy charisma and unique voice. It's a pleasure to see him shine with confidence and the most beautiful smile in the world. It is sheer bliss 
to listen to his fantastic voice, phenominal 
stability, crystal purity, sweet timbre and 
skillful command.

author: @liza_pet
text:
Every album, every comeback vocal of Seungmin goes to a new level, every song his voice shows new possibilities, literally every day he only becomes more beautiful and more beautiful 
like a rose under the rays of the sun, he dances amazingly, continuing to improve, gaining his own style.

author: @liza_pet
text:
Once again, Seungmin's parties are the 
juiciest and incredibly delicious, his voice 
is just something so unique and at the same 
time universal, absolutely any style suits him, which once again confirms how skillfully he 
owns it, and in addition to appearance, even in Seungmin's voice there is a frenzied charisma.

text: Seungmin is stunningly handsome, he really looks like a professional model and a handsome prince, flawless facial features, not a figure but perfection itself. author: @yjuggbfdyuiui6
text:
My name is Bao Xuezhen. I was born in Shanghai on January 18, 1950. I have a college degree. I worked as an engineer at a state-own enterprise, but I was fired from my job after the persecution of Falun Gong started in 1999. I now reside in Denmark.

I used to have many ailments and almost became incapacitated, but I recovered after I began practicing Falun Gong in May 1995. Because I refused to renounce my faith, I was sentenced to 3.5 years on June 1, 2001. I served time at the Shanghai Women’s Prison and was released at the end of 2004.

In early 2003, the prison conducted comprehensive physical examinations of all Falun Gong practitioners detained there. Years later, when I learned of the forced organ harvesting from living practitioners, I realized the checkups we had in 2003 were to see if any of us would be a good match for organ harvesting.

There were over 100 practitioners detained in the prison. I saw four buses parked outside of the entrance. All of them were equipped with advanced medical devices.

The Shanghai Women’s Prison had five wards and we lined up by the wards. Guards watched us while we waited and after we got on the buses one by one, to be examined. They examined us from head to toe, including our eyes, heart, liver, lungs, and kidneys. Samples of our blood and urine were collected. The blood draw tubes were really large. The doctors also did ultrasounds and gynecological exams on us.

While doing an ultrasound on me, the doctor appeared to be surprised. He called in several other doctors and guards to discuss my case. I heard one of them say, “It [referring to one of my organs] is useless. It’s full of stones, useless.” Then they asked me, “How do you feel in this area?” I didn’t respond. They looked at each other and didn’t say anything else.

It took them a few days to finish examining all the practitioners in the prison. Guard Shi Lei told us, “See how well the government treats you [Falun Gong practitioners] and offers such comprehensive examinations. Only you [Falun Gong practitioners] have such a ‘privilege.’ No one else has it, not even us prison guards.”

Back then, the horrific organ harvesting hadn’t been reported. But I noticed that shortly after the physical examinations, some practitioners who came from out of town but were arrested in Shanghai disappeared. These out-of-towners refused to reveal their names and were referred to by numbers. I thought they were transferred to other places, but now I realize that they may have been murdered for their organs.

A few days after the examination, the guards informed me that they needed to check my eyes again. I was puzzled as I didn’t have any problem with my eyes. They lied to my face, “Didn’t you ask to check your eyes?” I said, “When did I say that? My eyes are fine. Why do I want to have them checked?” The guards remained silent and dragged me to the prison entrance, waiting for a car to pick me up.

The car didn’t come. I kept asking why my eyes had to be re-examined but they didn’t answer. After waiting for about 20 minutes, the car still hadn’t arrived, so they took me back to the cell.

After I was released, I managed to flee to Denmark. In 2015, I did some investigation myself by calling Chinese hospitals. I said I was the family member of a patient who needed a transplant and I asked where the organs came from.

During a call I made to the Taizhou Hospital in Zhejiang Province in the first half of 2015, I was referred to doctor Wu Songjiang, a transplant expert. The person who answered the phone also suggested that I could go to Shanghai or contact the Zhejiang University School of Medicine for transplant, as both places had plenty of organs. They admitted that the organs were from Falun Gong practitioners and they could quickly match my blood type and schedule the transplant surgery.

author: @AngstyPenguin69
text:
Hi Stays, just in case you missed the reference. This came out the day after the Olympics opening ceremony, and in Changbin’s scene the store sign had the word “Olympus.” 

The Olympic games were part of a religious festival to honor Zeus, the Greek god who lived on Mount Olympus.  And the name "Olympics" derives from the word mountain — hence, the title of the song. 

And that’s why you also see some of the SKZ members climbing up a pyramid-looking mountain. 

The title, music video, lyrics, and release date of the song were all strategic. Stray Kids knew what they were doing and this is why I love them!!!

author: @TaliaCliche
text:
Here are some of the things I noticed in the MV:
- In the back you can see a store called Olympus Mons, which is also the name of a volcano on Mars.
- At 0:12 you can see Felix writing laws, things are organized and you can see screens in the back. At 1:17 Hyunjin is in the same room but it is now a disaster. The screen in the back has changed and snack leftovers are everywhere on the table (because they ATE?). At 3:01 the screen is back to normal.
- In the M/V they seem to be controlling the city. At 0:19 start storm clouds are visible over the city display and Felix pours water over it, and in Changbin's part you can see the rain. In 0:31 he puts the flaming monster truck in and when it switches to Hyunjin you can see the city is now on fire and there is the Monster Truck behind him. The idea of them controlling the city was proved at 1:51 when Seungmin puts his hand into the city. At the end in 3:02 you can see them watching over the now calm city. (I know for sure it is the city because if you look at the display you can still see the monster truck)

author: @srdv3317
text:
Клип вмещает в себя всю мощь ребят, что из раза в раз сотрясают всю музыкальную индустрию. Их путь с самого низа был труден и долог, а сейчас они недосягаемы и озаряют все вокруг. Stray Kids заслуживают самого лучшего, я верю, что многое в их карьере еще впереди. Ведь с каждым камбеком они поднимаются все выше, опережая самих себя, ставя новые рекорды. 
Очередной альбом попадает в самое сердце и теперь я безвылазно заслушиваю их треки. 

Восхищаюсь тем, в скольких жанрах они способны реализоваться, выбирая все новые звучания, но при этом сохраняя свой неповторимый стиль.

author: @BlueRose791
text: I love all the Greek Mythology references they sprinkled in here, with the Olympus Mons (Mount Olympus) convenience store, the lightning flashing around Changbin like Mighty Zeus making his mark in the mortal realm, and Lee Know’s close up with the lightening had a similar, though more lofty and intense effect. And I love the idea that Hans says to “Call them Pantheon,” the 12 main gods on Olympus, alluding that Stray Kids are now on a godlike level, using their music and multitude of talents to rule over the crowds. I also wonder whether or not the apple Felix was holding represents the apple of discord that caused a big fight between Hera, Aphrodite, and Athena over which god was the most beautiful of them all, which Aphrodite won. Perhaps Felix is the victor here? (˶ᵔ ᵕ ᵔ˶)  Overall, this is yet another triumph for Stray Kids, they absolutely ATE this song, and I’m looking forward to whatever comes next!

author: @AkshadaJoshi-w2f
text: Ok so few things i noticed which i think might mean something. Lee know topplin the chess piece which looks like the empire state Building, basically a symbol of authority, so it's them breaking the rules. The faces without eyes with constant smile with han running through them: fake people, maybe about the industry, about how so much of it is just for the sake of the camera, like in CHEESE. Just smile for the camera. Those lasers pointed at chan: skz being targeted so much by everyone. The apple that felix was holding, could be from the story of adam and eve, how their action of eating the apple gave them free will and gave the " Curse" Of knowledge. There are multiple points where they are standing on what seems like a elevated platform which seems like a mayan pyramid, again a symbol of authority and absolute power. The lyrics are definitely inspired form Zeus, the king of the Greek pantheon and the god of thunder. Thunder obvs has been used a lot in the mv. In the greek myths, zeus was abandoned on a mountain as a baby. But he grew up strong and later became the king of gods.and also the mountain here is mount olypus, the home of the greek gods. the shop behind changbin was also named olympus.  Did i miss smthng?
